European Coal Prices Fall 0.5%, Head for Second Straight Decline

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-05-16T08:47:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/european-coal-prices-fall-0-5-head-for-second-straight-decline.html
European coal derivatives fell, on
course for a second consecutive decline.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year retreated 60 cents, or 0.5 percent, to
$125.75 a metric ton by 9:37 a.m. in  London . Prices have slid
2.9 percent in the past week.  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
